pathVariables.accessToken: a unique string that resolves to a given externalFileResource

/externalFileResources/{accessToken}.description:
Returns a file associated with the externalFileResource resolved from the accessToken.

Only files contained in externalFileResources with a valid accessToken, expiration date null or in the future are files allowed to be served trough this endpoint.

/organisationUnitLocations/orgUnitByLoca.description: Get lowest level Org Units that includes the location in their polygon shape.

/dataStore/{namespace}.description: Returns a list of strings representing keys in the given namespace.
Deletes all keys with the given namespace.

/userDataStore.description: Returns a JSON array of strings representing the different namespaces used. If no namespaces exist, an empty array is returned.

/staticContent/{key}.description: Serves the PNG associated with the key. If custom logo is not used the request will redirect to the default.
Uploads PNG images based on a key. Only accepts PNG and white listed keys.

/trackedEntityAttributes/{id}/generate.description: This method is legacy and will do the same as generateAndReserveValues, but with only 3 days expiration. The use-case for this endpoint is to get a single id when filling in the form, so we assume the form is submitted within 3 days. generateAndReserveValues is designed to account for offline devices that need to reserve ids in batches for a longer period of time.

/dataStore/{namespace}/{key}/metaData.description: Retrieves the KeyJsonValue represented by the given key from the given namespace.

/reports/jasperReports/img.description: This methods wraps the Jasper image servlet to avoid having a separate servlet mapping around. Note that the path to images are relative to the reports path in this controller.

/userDataStore/{namespace}/{key}.description: Retrieves the value of the KeyJsonValue represented by the given key and namespace from the current user.
Creates a new KeyJsonValue Object on the current user with the key, namespace and value supplied.

/dataStore.description: Returns a JSON array of strings representing the different namespaces used. If no namespaces exist, an empty array is returned.

/dataStore/{namespace}/{key}.description: Creates a new KeyJsonValue Object on the given namespace with the key and value supplied.
Update a key in the given namespace.
Delete a key from the given namespace.

/files{/style, /style/external}.description: The style/external mapping enables style to be reached from login page / before authentication.

/userDataStore/{namespace}.description: Returns a JSON array of strings representing the different keys used in a given namespace. If no namespaces exist, an empty array is returned.
Deletes all keys with the given user and namespace.

/organisationUnitLocations/withinRange.description: Get Organisation Units within a distance from a location

pathVariables.uid: the unique id of the file resource

/audits/files/{uid}.description: Returns the file with the given uid

/organisationUnitLocations/locationWithi.description: Check if the location lies within the organisation unit boundary
